	a <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Node: CACNG2 | UniProt: Q9Y698 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons, CHO cells, rat/hippocampal slice culture | Perturbation: none, mut (S9A), mut (S9D), mut (S9D-delta4) | Assay: metabolic labeling, 2D-TLC phosphopeptide mapping, SDS-PAGE mobility shift, Western blot with lambda-phosphatase | Fig: 1A-B, 2A-F | Note: Stargazin phosphorylated on 9 conserved cytoplasmic Ser residues (Ser only, no Thr/Tyr); PSD fraction preferentially phosphorylated; S9A abolishes all phosphorylation; S9D mimics mobility shift; basal phosphorylation half-life ~1 hr (staurosporine, Fig 4A)"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: PPP3CA -> PPP1CA | Relation: positively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (FK506) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4G | Note: PP2B acts partly upstream of PP1; FK506 partially blocks NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: PPP1CA -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly negatively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (tautomycin) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4F | Note: PP1 mediates NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation; tautomycin completely blocks it; Ca2+-dependent"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: DLG4 | UniProt: P78352 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: rat/hippocampal slice culture | Perturbation: mut (S9D-delta4, phosphomimic lacking PDZ site) | Assay: paired whole-cell recording | Fig: 3E | Note: PSD-95 PDZ interaction required for phosphorylated STG to enhance synaptic AMPA currents; S9D-delta4 depresses AMPA EPSC"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: PRKCA | UniProt: P17252 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: none, pharmacol (GF109203X) | Assay: in vitro kinase assay, SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 5B-C | Note: PKC directly phosphorylates STG tail more efficiently than histone; GF109203X blocks STG rephosphorylation in neurons after NMDA washout"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , """Node: PPP1CA | UniProt: P36873 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (tautomycin) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4A,4F | Note: PP1 mediates both basal and NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation; tautomycin completely blocks both
"""^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: CAMK2A | UniProt: Q9UQM7 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: none, pharmacol (KN93) | Assay: in vitro kinase assay, SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 5B-C | Note: CaMKII directly phosphorylates purified STG C-terminal tail with efficiency comparable to GluR1 tail; KN93 blocks STG rephosphorylation in neurons after NMDA washout"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Node: PPP3CA | UniProt: Q08209 | PMID: 15664178 | Model: mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: pharmacol (FK506) | Assay: SDS-PAGE mobility shift | Fig: 4A,4G | Note: PP2B partially blocks NMDA-induced STG dephosphorylation; acts partly upstream of PP1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: PRKCA -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: none (in vitro), pharmacol (GF109203X, cellular) | Assay: in vitro kinase assay (direct), SDS-PAGE mobility shift (cellular) | Fig: 5B-C | Note: Direct phosphorylation of STG tail in vitro (more efficient than histone); confirmed in neurons where GF109203X blocks rephosphorylation after NMDA washout"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , "Edge: CAMK2A -> CACNG2 | Relation: directly positively regulates | PMID: 15664178 | Model: purified recombinant proteins, mouse/cerebrocortical neurons | Perturbation: none (in vitro), pharmacol (KN93, cellular) | Assay: in vitro kinase assay (direct), SDS-PAGE mobility shift (cellular) | Fig: 5B-C | Note: Direct phosphorylation of STG tail in vitro; confirmed in neurons where KN93 blocks rephosphorylation after NMDA washout"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title> """NMDAR-dependent recruitment of AMPA receptor to clathrin adaptor complex - Mouse
"""^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
